description: In collaboration with #MagnumPH, I am honored to partner with them to spread the word that Magnum Ice Cream now has a certified vegan ice-cream bar in the Philippines. “Magnum Non-Dairy Almond” is available at most grocery stores and convenience stores all over the Philippines, not just Manila! This is great news, especially for those who live in a city or barangay where vegan options may not be as accessible. I was tasked to show recipes that people can use to play up this treat and naturally I thought of Filipino flavors -Champorado style, Halo-halo style, and fried Turon ice cream. My favorite is the Halo-halo, while my husband prefers the fried ice cream, while my 12-year-old nephew loves the Champorado. In the video, I’m also going to show how to make vegan whipped cream from scratch, so you can use it to dress up your bar. I hope you’ll enjoy the results as much I enjoyed putting these recipes for you. Maraming salamat to Magnum for partnering and for thinking of our kababayans who are ready and hungry for more vegan options in the Philippines. Kain na, let’s eat! #MagnumDairyFree #MagnumPH #astigvegan #veganfilipino
fulltitle: Magnum Dairy-Free now available in the Philippines!
